comments.body:
latest powershell package has WSMAN PSRP Client that can connect from Linux and OSX to Windows. Basic authentication is supported at this time, and on Windows you will need to have a local machine account that is configured as administrator. You will also need to configure WinRM to turn on support for basic auth on the server. If you don't have WinRM set up with SSL then you will also need to enable unencrypted server traffic for the server.
